NOTE /SegmentIndex

                                                                                                                                                                                            


1
00:00:09.276 --> 00:00:11.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[muffled shouting]

2
00:00:11.156 --> 00:00:12.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Look, save your energy.

3
00:00:12.955 --> 00:00:15.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll have you out of there
as soon as possible.

4
00:00:17.744 --> 00:00:18.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope.

5
00:00:20.992 --> 00:00:22.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Try rerouting
the power coupling.

6
00:00:26.951 --> 00:00:28.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. O'Brien.

7
00:00:28.631 --> 00:00:30.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
See if you can activate
the interlock servos.

8
00:00:30.910 --> 00:00:32.309 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. O'Brien.

9
00:00:32.389 --> 00:00:35.909 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain Jaheel, those people
have been stuck in that air lock

10
00:00:35.988 --> 00:00:37.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for over an hour.

11
00:00:37.388 --> 00:00:39.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, if you can wait
till we get that door opened

12
00:00:39.547 --> 00:00:41.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll be happy to listen
to any problems you might have.

13
00:00:41.787 --> 00:00:44.466 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I've already been waiting two days
for your people to readjust

14
00:00:44.546 --> 00:00:46.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
my ship's antimatter flow converter.

15
00:00:46.705 --> 00:00:49.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm afraid we've gotten a little behind
in our maintenance schedule.

16
00:00:49.704 --> 00:00:51.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not interested in hearing excuses.

17
00:00:51.423 --> 00:00:54.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have a shipment of Tamen Sahsheer
waiting to be delivered to Largo V,

18
00:00:54.663 --> 00:00:57.622 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I'll need to do better than warp 1
to get there before it spoils.

19
00:00:57.702 --> 00:01:01.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll try to get a repair crew
to you by the end of the day.

20
00:01:01.460 --> 00:01:02.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now, that's the best I can do.

21
00:01:02.900 --> 00:01:05.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your best, Mr. O'Brien,
hardly seems good enough.

22
00:01:08.978 --> 00:01:10.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[woman]<i> Dax to O'Brien.</i>

23
00:01:10.617 --> 00:01:12.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
O'Brien here.

24
00:01:12.177 --> 00:01:13.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Can you spare a minute, Chief?</i>

25
00:01:13.417 --> 00:01:15.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I have a little problem here at the lab.</i>

26
00:01:17.559 --> 00:01:18.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On my way.

27
00:01:24.294 --> 00:01:25.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks for coming, Chief.

28
00:01:25.693 --> 00:01:27.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you doing out here?

29
00:01:29.772 --> 00:01:31.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[loud whining]

30
00:01:34.531 --> 00:01:36.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have you checked the EPS converter?

31
00:01:36.570 --> 00:01:38.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, first thing.

32
00:01:38.130 --> 00:01:40.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How about the intensity grid?
-It's fine.

33
00:01:40.489 --> 00:01:43.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then it's probably the secondary
phase modulator.

34
00:01:43.248 --> 00:01:46.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We had trouble with them last week
in the main power core.

35
00:01:48.567 --> 00:01:50.869 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That should do it.

36
00:01:50.166 --> 00:01:51.859 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[noise stops]

37
00:01:55.446 --> 00:01:56.844 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Anything else I can do for you?

38
00:01:59.433 --> 00:02:02.403 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The navigational computer
hasn't worked reliably for three days.

39
00:02:02.482 --> 00:02:05.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I ask for the star charts
for the Argosian sector--

40
00:02:05.201 --> 00:02:07.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Glessene sector
comes up instead.

41
00:02:07.601 --> 00:02:10.160 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's when I can coax
this system on line.

42
00:02:10.240 --> 00:02:11.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[O'Brien] Uh-huh.

43
00:02:11.600 --> 00:02:13.319 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Try it now.

44
00:02:15.238 --> 00:02:17.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh! That's more like it.

45
00:02:27.235 --> 00:02:29.474 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You look like you
could use some sleep.

46
00:02:29.555 --> 00:02:30.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who has time for sleep?

47
00:02:31.833 --> 00:02:34.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd settle for five minutes
peace and quiet.

48
00:02:38.323 --> 00:02:40.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Chief, I thought you were going
to fix the replicators.

49
00:02:41.670 --> 00:02:43.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're absolutely right, sir.

50
00:02:43.910 --> 00:02:45.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I knew I'd forgotten something.

51
00:02:45.549 --> 00:02:48.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Can't have the Operations Chief
sitting around daydreaming

52
00:02:48.189 --> 00:02:50.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
when there's work
to be done, can we?

53
00:02:50.188 --> 00:02:52.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ho, ho, ho, ho.
I'll get right on it.

54
00:02:54.787 --> 00:02:57.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Fix the replicators, Chief."

55
00:02:57.146 --> 00:02:59.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"My console's off-line, Chief."

56
00:02:59.105 --> 00:03:00.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groaning]

57
00:03:00.545 --> 00:03:02.984 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I should have transferred
to a cargo drone--

58
00:03:03.644 --> 00:03:05.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no people, no complaints.

59
00:03:26.857 --> 00:03:28.217 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

60
00:03:35.895 --> 00:03:37.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[instrument humming]

61
00:03:43.932 --> 00:03:46.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hot coffee-- black, double sweet.

62
00:04:15.882 --> 00:04:17.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

63
00:06:10.568 --> 00:06:12.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Odo] Tell me, Quark.

64
00:06:12.208 --> 00:06:16.327 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Am I mistaken, or is business
a little slow today?

65
00:06:16.566 --> 00:06:20.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Slow? It's been almost nonexistent
for the past three days.

66
00:06:20.645 --> 00:06:22.645 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Mmm. Who knows?

67
00:06:23.484 --> 00:06:27.163 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
If things don't improve
you may be forced to close down.

68
00:06:27.243 --> 00:06:28.803 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Oh, you'd like that, wouldn't you?

69
00:06:28.882 --> 00:06:33.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Well, let's just say, without you around
my job would be considerably easier.

70
00:06:33.841 --> 00:06:36.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Without me around,
you'd be forced to find

71
00:06:36.640 --> 00:06:39.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
some other poor innocent to persecute.

72
00:06:39.439 --> 00:06:43.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Think about that while you sit here
gloating at my misfortune.

73
00:06:43.718 --> 00:06:44.757 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Quark!

74
00:06:44.838 --> 00:06:47.378 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You call this Kohlian stew?

75
00:06:52.755 --> 00:06:57.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
If your meal isn't satisfactory
I'm sure we could, uh, exchange it

76
00:06:57.753 --> 00:06:59.234 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
for something more to your liking.

77
00:06:59.514 --> 00:07:04.327 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Aren't you the least bit curious
as to how it tastes?

78
00:07:06.551 --> 00:07:08.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[groaning]

79
00:07:09.710 --> 00:07:10.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Now...

80
00:07:10.390 --> 00:07:11.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you served it.

81
00:07:11.710 --> 00:07:12.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're going to eat it.

82
00:07:13.699 --> 00:07:15.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right, that's enough.

83
00:07:16.286 --> 00:07:17.388 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I said, eat it!

84
00:07:19.268 --> 00:07:20.707 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I said...

85
00:07:21.307 --> 00:07:22.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
that's enough.

86
00:07:23.387 --> 00:07:24.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Leave him alone.

87
00:07:29.304 --> 00:07:32.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Well, another satisfied customer.

88
00:07:34.663 --> 00:07:36.702 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's these replicators.

89
00:07:36.782 --> 00:07:39.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I don't get them fixed soon,
they'll destroy my business.

90
00:07:39.341 --> 00:07:41.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why not get O'Brien to fix them?

91
00:07:41.220 --> 00:07:44.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He has the replicators on
the command level working perfectly.

92
00:07:44.500 --> 00:07:46.699 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm on his waiting list.

93
00:07:46.779 --> 00:07:49.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He assures me he'll get to them
as soon as he can.

94
00:07:50.184 --> 00:07:51.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mmm...

95
00:07:51.338 --> 00:07:53.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No telling when that will be.

96
00:07:53.538 --> 00:07:55.776 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Chief's a very busy man.

97
00:08:00.615 --> 00:08:02.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer...

98
00:08:02.894 --> 00:08:04.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
display a station layout.

99
00:08:06.333 --> 00:08:09.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Highlight locations
of all repaired replicators

100
00:08:09.772 --> 00:08:11.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
on command level.

101
00:08:11.292 --> 00:08:12.412 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on machine]
<i>Information restricted</i>

102
00:08:12.491 --> 00:08:14.851 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>to security clearance 5 and above.</i>

103
00:08:14.931 --> 00:08:17.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Please enter security verification.</i>

104
00:08:32.525 --> 00:08:34.325 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Clearance verified.</i>

105
00:08:46.815 --> 00:08:47.241 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There you go, sir.

106
00:08:47.321 --> 00:08:49.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think you'll find that
more to your liking.

107
00:08:50.280 --> 00:08:52.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very much appreciated, Mr. O'Brien.

108
00:08:52.480 --> 00:08:53.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't mention it, sir.

109
00:08:53.559 --> 00:08:55.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unfortunately,
there are plenty of replicators

110
00:08:55.438 --> 00:08:57.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
around the station
that still need looking after.

111
00:08:58.118 --> 00:08:59.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You all right, Chief?

112
00:09:00.318 --> 00:09:01.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm just a bit hot.

113
00:09:02.317 --> 00:09:04.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The environmental controls
must be acting up again.

114
00:09:04.916 --> 00:09:06.316 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Send my regards to Mrs. O'Brien.

115
00:09:06.395 --> 00:09:08.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jake tells me she's a wonderful teacher.

116
00:09:08.154 --> 00:09:09.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, that's nice to hear, sir.

117
00:09:09.874 --> 00:09:11.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's flower units about the lad herself.

118
00:09:11.593 --> 00:09:12.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excuse me?

119
00:09:13.733 --> 00:09:13.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sir?

120
00:09:14.733 --> 00:09:15.552 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What was that you just said?

121
00:09:16.512 --> 00:09:20.712 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's... quite fond of the lad herself.

122
00:09:20.791 --> 00:09:21.990 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

123
00:09:22.712 --> 00:09:23.590 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm glad to hear it.

124
00:09:23.670 --> 00:09:25.702 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very good, sir.

125
00:09:32.788 --> 00:09:34.267 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man] Ladies.

126
00:09:34.347 --> 00:09:35.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello, Lieutenant.

127
00:09:36.787 --> 00:09:39.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I forgot how different it was.

128
00:09:39.386 --> 00:09:40.945 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How different what was?

129
00:09:41.225 --> 00:09:42.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Being female.

130
00:09:42.864 --> 00:09:44.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't been one for over 80 years.

131
00:09:45.583 --> 00:09:46.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All this attention.

132
00:09:46.703 --> 00:09:48.383 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Imagine it must take
some getting used to.

133
00:09:48.462 --> 00:09:50.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Actually, I find it quite enjoyable.

134
00:09:50.142 --> 00:09:51.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Major Kira.

135
00:09:51.542 --> 00:09:52.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lieutenant Dax.

136
00:09:53.502 --> 00:09:56.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd be honored to have you
join my little party--

137
00:09:56.820 --> 00:09:58.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
as my guests, of course.

138
00:09:58.380 --> 00:09:59.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's all this, Quark?

139
00:09:59.979 --> 00:10:02.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You cheat your 1,000th customer?

140
00:10:02.219 --> 00:10:04.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Who says Bajorans
don't have a sense of humor?

141
00:10:05.218 --> 00:10:10.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Actually, uh, we're celebrating the repair
of the bar's replicator system.

142
00:10:10.616 --> 00:10:13.135 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perhaps I could interest you

143
00:10:13.215 --> 00:10:16.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in a nice, double-whipped,
I'danian spice pudding.

144
00:10:17.214 --> 00:10:18.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, what do you think?

145
00:10:19.144 --> 00:10:20.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think I'm due back at Ops

146
00:10:20.933 --> 00:10:22.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but, uh, go on.

147
00:10:22.372 --> 00:10:23.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Enjoy yourself.

148
00:10:35.449 --> 00:10:36.608 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chief?

149
00:10:37.208 --> 00:10:38.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[slurring] How can I help you, Major?

150
00:10:40.967 --> 00:10:43.868 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Looks like you're the one
who could use a little help.

151
00:10:43.726 --> 00:10:45.606 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, no, I'm fine, really.

152
00:10:49.565 --> 00:10:51.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I suppose this isn't
a good time to tell you

153
00:10:51.724 --> 00:10:54.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that number three turbolift
has broken down again.

154
00:10:58.162 --> 00:10:59.842 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Joking, Chief.

155
00:11:01.361 --> 00:11:03.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Major, lark's true pepper.

156
00:11:04.160 --> 00:11:05.280 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

157
00:11:07.999 --> 00:11:10.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let birds go further loose maybe.

158
00:11:11.797 --> 00:11:12.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shout easy play.

159
00:11:13.373 --> 00:11:15.636 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chief, you're not making any sense.

160
00:11:15.717 --> 00:11:17.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Round the turbulent quick.

161
00:11:21.834 --> 00:11:23.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, close the reverse harbor.

162
00:11:27.633 --> 00:11:30.712 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A-Ankle try sound.

163
00:11:31.392 --> 00:11:33.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Reset gleaming.

164
00:11:35.191 --> 00:11:36.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
D-Dinner to bug.

165
00:11:39.590 --> 00:11:41.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chief, wait.

166
00:11:41.629 --> 00:11:42.828 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When?

167
00:11:42.909 --> 00:11:43.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chief.

168
00:11:56.465 --> 00:11:59.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, continue neural imaging scan

169
00:11:59.703 --> 00:12:01.383 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and stimulate visual cortex.

170
00:12:01.463 --> 00:12:03.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female automated voice]
<i>All visual responses normal.</i>

171
00:12:08.941 --> 00:12:10.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Begin auditory stimuli.

172
00:12:10.820 --> 00:12:12.660 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[woman]<i> No physiological damage.</i>

173
00:12:12.739 --> 00:12:15.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>All brain functions</i>
<i>within normal parameters.</i>

174
00:12:17.178 --> 00:12:18.737 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Nurse.
-Yes?

175
00:12:19.498 --> 00:12:22.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Will you pull up Mr. O'Brien's
neurophysiological history, please?

176
00:12:22.136 --> 00:12:23.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, Doctor.

177
00:12:31.254 --> 00:12:33.137 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is that? What's he written?

178
00:12:33.942 --> 00:12:34.373 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wish I knew.

179
00:12:35.413 --> 00:12:38.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Strike limits flame the dark true salt.

180
00:12:38.692 --> 00:12:39.932 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please, Chief, take a seat.

181
00:12:40.116 --> 00:12:41.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Way link complete.

182
00:12:41.731 --> 00:12:43.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Way link!

183
00:12:46.289 --> 00:12:47.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's wrong with him?

184
00:12:47.849 --> 00:12:50.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He appears to suffering
from a form of aphasia.

185
00:12:50.208 --> 00:12:51.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a perceptual dysfunction

186
00:12:51.528 --> 00:12:55.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in which aural and visual stimuli
are incorrectly processed by the brain.

187
00:12:55.127 --> 00:12:57.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His actual thinking hasn't been affected

188
00:12:57.446 --> 00:12:59.458 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but he's incapable of expressing himself

189
00:12:59.126 --> 00:13:01.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
or understanding others.

190
00:13:01.605 --> 00:13:04.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Victory strike limits frosted wake.

191
00:13:06.163 --> 00:13:08.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Simple hesitation!

192
00:13:09.243 --> 00:13:10.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not sure I follow you, Doctor.

193
00:13:10.962 --> 00:13:12.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You say Mr. O'Brien is aphasiac

194
00:13:12.442 --> 00:13:13.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but all of his tests
have come up negative.

195
00:13:15.480 --> 00:13:19.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Isn't aphasia typically associated
with some kind of cranial trauma?

196
00:13:19.439 --> 00:13:22.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes. It can occur as a result of a stroke
or a blow to the head.

197
00:13:22.839 --> 00:13:24.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But there's no evidence of that here.

198
00:13:24.318 --> 00:13:26.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Did you check the medical library
for any precedents?

199
00:13:26.757 --> 00:13:29.636 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And rechecked-- nothing, so far.

200
00:13:29.717 --> 00:13:30.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have any theories?

201
00:13:31.556 --> 00:13:32.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not yet.

202
00:13:32.875 --> 00:13:34.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Find one.

203
00:13:34.435 --> 00:13:36.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major Kira, get a hold
of the Chief's personal duty log.

204
00:13:37.344 --> 00:13:39.834 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I want to know where he's been
and what he's done for the past 52 hours.

205
00:13:39.913 --> 00:13:43.112 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've already examined it, Commander.
He's been all over this station.

206
00:13:43.192 --> 00:13:45.712 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Retrace his steps and see what
you come up with.

207
00:13:45.951 --> 00:13:49.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dax, you will temporarily assume
Mr. O'Brien's duties.

208
00:13:49.470 --> 00:13:51.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, uh... Um...

209
00:13:51.350 --> 00:13:53.109 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is there a problem, Lieutenant?

210
00:13:54.229 --> 00:13:55.709 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lieutenant?

211
00:13:56.989 --> 00:13:59.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry, Benjamin.

212
00:13:59.868 --> 00:14:01.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm unable to...

213
00:14:03.147 --> 00:14:05.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
foolish assembled regal...

214
00:14:06.225 --> 00:14:07.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
control weather.

215
00:14:18.261 --> 00:14:22.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Spontaneous development of aphasia
is virtually impossible.

216
00:14:22.341 --> 00:14:25.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yet we saw Lieutenant Dax
become aphasiac before our eyes.

217
00:14:25.660 --> 00:14:27.179 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This told me we were
dealing with a disease

218
00:14:27.259 --> 00:14:28.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
which only mimics aphasia,

219
00:14:29.938 --> 00:14:33.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so I ran a full neural synaptic comparison
between Dax and O'Brien

220
00:14:33.257 --> 00:14:35.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I found this in the temporal lobes
of both patients.

221
00:14:35.856 --> 00:14:36.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A virus.

222
00:14:37.965 --> 00:14:39.855 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It imposes itself
within the established synaptic pathways

223
00:14:39.935 --> 00:14:41.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and then randomly reroutes them.

224
00:14:41.815 --> 00:14:44.334 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For example, when I look at this,

225
00:14:44.974 --> 00:14:46.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a process occurs within my brain

226
00:14:46.933 --> 00:14:49.292 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
which connects the stimulus
to the word "tricorder."

227
00:14:49.373 --> 00:14:51.332 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This virus disrupts that process.

228
00:14:51.892 --> 00:14:53.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd see a tricorder

229
00:14:53.731 --> 00:14:56.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I'd say something ridiculous,
like "window."

230
00:14:56.491 --> 00:14:57.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Exactly.

231
00:14:57.730 --> 00:14:59.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doctor, I think you should get over here.

232
00:14:59.289 --> 00:15:01.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Night the flow trade again.
-You lost pile luck.

233
00:15:01.249 --> 00:15:03.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Away tunnel back the garden.

234
00:15:03.248 --> 00:15:05.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doctor, I want this station

235
00:15:05.883 --> 00:15:07.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
put under emergency quarantine
immediately.

236
00:15:07.167 --> 00:15:08.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

237
00:15:12.565 --> 00:15:15.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[conversation and music]

238
00:15:15.444 --> 00:15:16.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man] Dabo!

239
00:15:16.604 --> 00:15:17.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[shouting]

240
00:15:23.682 --> 00:15:27.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quark, what is going on here?

241
00:15:28.159 --> 00:15:29.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What does it look like?

242
00:15:29.521 --> 00:15:31.759 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It looks like business as usual

243
00:15:31.840 --> 00:15:33.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but that's impossible

244
00:15:33.199 --> 00:15:36.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because all shops and businesses
have been closed until further notice.

245
00:15:36.598 --> 00:15:39.437 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Except, of course,
for essential station operations.

246
00:15:39.518 --> 00:15:41.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For which this place hardly qualifies.

247
00:15:41.997 --> 00:15:43.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't think they'd agree.

248
00:15:43.436 --> 00:15:46.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This quarantine has everybody
on edge, Constable.

249
00:15:46.355 --> 00:15:49.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Would you deprive them
of a little harmless diversion?

250
00:15:53.713 --> 00:15:56.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They'd be safer in their quarters.

251
00:15:56.953 --> 00:16:00.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quark, this Kohlian stew-- magnificent.

252
00:16:00.911 --> 00:16:04.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Fortunately, my assistant, Rom,
was able to fix the replicators.

253
00:16:06.550 --> 00:16:10.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes... Very fortunate.

254
00:16:27.583 --> 00:16:28.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sisko] Jake...

255
00:16:28.863 --> 00:16:30.502 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I expected you home an hour ago.

256
00:16:30.582 --> 00:16:32.221 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry. I was at Nog's.

257
00:16:32.742 --> 00:16:34.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dad, about this quarantine--

258
00:16:34.421 --> 00:16:35.780 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
it's going to be OK, isn't it?

259
00:16:35.861 --> 00:16:37.500 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's just a precaution, nothing more.

260
00:16:37.580 --> 00:16:39.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Jaheel] I wish I shared your
confidence, Commander.

261
00:16:40.579 --> 00:16:41.979 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go straight home, son.

262
00:16:42.595 --> 00:16:43.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll see you at dinner.

263
00:16:44.618 --> 00:16:47.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain Jaheel, all visitors
have been confined to their ships.

264
00:16:47.937 --> 00:16:49.976 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Believe me,
there is no place I'd rather be.

265
00:16:50.565 --> 00:16:51.216 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then what are you doing here?

266
00:16:51.815 --> 00:16:54.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander, I officially request permission
to leave this station.

267
00:16:55.152 --> 00:16:56.151 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Request denied.

268
00:16:56.947 --> 00:16:58.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But none of my crew
has been affected by this virus of yours.

269
00:16:58.693 --> 00:17:02.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And unless I depart at once
my whole cargo will be ruined!

270
00:17:02.293 --> 00:17:06.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, I suggest
you return to your ship now.

271
00:17:07.571 --> 00:17:11.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please. I don't want to get sick.

272
00:17:12.450 --> 00:17:16.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sorry, but until we can
find a cure for this... thing,

273
00:17:16.568 --> 00:17:17.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no one's going anywhere.

274
00:17:39.522 --> 00:17:40.921 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer,

275
00:17:41.681 --> 00:17:46.320 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
let's start with one
Ferengi Starduster, please.

276
00:17:46.399 --> 00:17:47.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Extra strong.

277
00:17:55.716 --> 00:17:56.876 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perfect.

278
00:18:01.635 --> 00:18:05.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh... I thought the front wheels
were sticking a bit.

279
00:18:05.274 --> 00:18:09.393 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unauthorized access
to crew quarters is a crime, Quark.

280
00:18:09.472 --> 00:18:12.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You could have just asked
to use the replicators.

281
00:18:12.871 --> 00:18:16.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's an old Ferengi saying--
"Never ask when you can take."

282
00:18:17.270 --> 00:18:19.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, how did you figure it out?

283
00:18:19.790 --> 00:18:22.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You claimed Rom fixed your replicators.

284
00:18:22.748 --> 00:18:24.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-So?
-Rom's an idiot.

285
00:18:24.548 --> 00:18:26.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He couldn't fix a straw if it was bent.

286
00:18:27.267 --> 00:18:29.507 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're right. Rom is an idiot.

287
00:18:30.666 --> 00:18:33.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Remind me to get rid of him tomorrow.

288
00:18:35.825 --> 00:18:38.623 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Based on the levels of the virus
found in the patients' blood,

289
00:18:38.704 --> 00:18:40.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I believe it's being
absorbed through ingestion.

290
00:18:40.823 --> 00:18:42.622 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You're saying it's in our food?
-Well, that's not possible.

291
00:18:42.703 --> 00:18:46.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All the food on this station is replicated
and all the replicators use biofilters.

292
00:18:46.581 --> 00:18:49.661 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They automatically screen out contaminants
including viruses.

293
00:18:49.740 --> 00:18:53.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major, I've analyzed samples
from replicators all over the station.

294
00:18:53.859 --> 00:18:55.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Food on the command level is contaminated.

295
00:18:55.778 --> 00:18:57.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But all of us here have
eaten from those replicators.

296
00:18:58.587 --> 00:18:59.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How come we're not aphasic?

297
00:18:59.337 --> 00:19:01.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This virus is highly adaptable.

298
00:19:01.137 --> 00:19:04.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Its incubation period
seems to vary within each individual.

299
00:19:04.776 --> 00:19:06.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
According to O'Brien's duty log

300
00:19:06.816 --> 00:19:08.934 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the last thing he did
before becoming aphasic

301
00:19:09.154 --> 00:19:10.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
was fix the command level replicators.

302
00:19:11.949 --> 00:19:13.974 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Get a repair crew over there
to inspect the site.

303
00:19:14.133 --> 00:19:15.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's shut down those replicators.

304
00:19:16.173 --> 00:19:18.252 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe we'll be able
to limit further contamination.

305
00:19:18.332 --> 00:19:20.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm afraid that's not going to do it, sir.

306
00:19:20.531 --> 00:19:23.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been getting aphasic patients
from all over the station.

307
00:19:23.291 --> 00:19:24.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How is that possible?

308
00:19:24.490 --> 00:19:25.570 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can thank Quark.

309
00:19:25.649 --> 00:19:28.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I caught him using a replicator
in one of the vacant crew quarters.

310
00:19:28.808 --> 00:19:30.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He was producing
his entire menu out of there.

311
00:19:33.877 --> 00:19:35.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If this virus is present

312
00:19:35.847 --> 00:19:38.566 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
within a large enough segment
of the population

313
00:19:39.464 --> 00:19:40.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
it could mean...

314
00:19:41.684 --> 00:19:43.204 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is it, Doctor?

315
00:19:44.484 --> 00:19:46.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just took an air sample.

316
00:19:48.163 --> 00:19:49.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sisko] The virus...

317
00:19:50.433 --> 00:19:51.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's mutated into an airborne variety.

318
00:19:51.841 --> 00:19:53.205 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which means?

319
00:19:53.241 --> 00:19:56.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which means the whole station is infected.

320
00:20:05.398 --> 00:20:08.797 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sisko]<i> Station Log, Stardate 46423.7.</i>

321
00:20:08.877 --> 00:20:13.361 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Nearly 60% of DS9's population</i>
<i>has now contracted the aphasia virus.</i>

322
00:20:13.115 --> 00:20:15.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We've initiated standard</i>
<i>quarantine procedures</i>

323
00:20:15.515 --> 00:20:17.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and are advising all incoming ships</i>

324
00:20:17.274 --> 00:20:18.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to maintain their distance</i>
<i>from the station</i>

325
00:20:19.744 --> 00:20:20.713 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>until further notice.</i>

326
00:20:40.628 --> 00:20:44.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I found it in the replicator's
pattern generator.

327
00:20:44.386 --> 00:20:47.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
O'Brien must have accidentally
triggered it when he repaired the system.

328
00:20:47.225 --> 00:20:51.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
According to Bashir, it introduced
an anomalous programming sequence

329
00:20:51.184 --> 00:20:53.183 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
into the materialization subroutine.

330
00:20:53.263 --> 00:20:55.103 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In effect, it built the virus

331
00:20:55.182 --> 00:20:58.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
directly into the replicated food
at a molecular level.

332
00:20:58.622 --> 00:21:01.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-So what we have here is sabotage.
-Cardassian sabotage.

333
00:21:01.221 --> 00:21:04.140 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How can you be sure?
-Has a diboridium core for a power source.

334
00:21:04.220 --> 00:21:06.100 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That is Cardassian technology.

335
00:21:06.540 --> 00:21:08.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man]<i> Bashir to Sisko.</i>

336
00:21:09.139 --> 00:21:10.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sisko here.

337
00:21:10.499 --> 00:21:12.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[man]<i> Commander, I think you'd better</i>
<i>get down here to the infirmary</i>

338
00:21:12.617 --> 00:21:13.658 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>as soon as possible.</i>

339
00:21:13.737 --> 00:21:14.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On my way.

340
00:21:20.415 --> 00:21:22.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You wanted to see me, Doctor?

341
00:21:24.534 --> 00:21:25.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jake?

342
00:21:26.654 --> 00:21:29.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Left... become better...

343
00:21:29.653 --> 00:21:32.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
control... entire hope.

344
00:21:35.851 --> 00:21:37.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Bashir] We've converted
some empty crew quarters

345
00:21:37.730 --> 00:21:38.730 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
into a hospital ward.

346
00:21:38.810 --> 00:21:39.810 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He'll be well looked after.

347
00:21:39.889 --> 00:21:41.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll take him there myself.

348
00:21:42.169 --> 00:21:44.128 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come on, Jake.
You're going to be all right.

349
00:21:44.208 --> 00:21:48.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander, when you've got a moment,
I've found something I'd like to show you.

350
00:21:52.846 --> 00:21:54.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[people muttering]

351
00:21:54.125 --> 00:21:56.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[woman] It'll be all right.
Just lay back.

352
00:21:56.685 --> 00:21:57.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[coughing]

353
00:21:57.884 --> 00:22:00.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[woman] I know,
but just lay back and relax.

354
00:22:02.362 --> 00:22:05.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark] Food... dabo... drinks...

355
00:22:05.521 --> 00:22:08.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
money... hand... mine... give!

356
00:22:08.881 --> 00:22:12.639 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, Quark, I see even you couldn't
weasel your way clear of this one.

357
00:22:12.720 --> 00:22:15.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You underestimate the Ferengi
immune system, Commander.

358
00:22:15.639 --> 00:22:18.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm merely here visiting
my less fortunate customers

359
00:22:18.278 --> 00:22:19.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to make sure they're
not faking the illness

360
00:22:20.777 --> 00:22:21.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to avoid paying their bills.

361
00:22:21.557 --> 00:22:22.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No one could be that devious.

362
00:22:23.767 --> 00:22:23.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am.

363
00:22:24.767 --> 00:22:27.755 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You... gold... owe... me!

364
00:22:30.435 --> 00:22:32.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[indistinct conversation]

365
00:22:32.594 --> 00:22:34.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark] I... now... give...

366
00:22:35.633 --> 00:22:36.912 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Up!

367
00:22:39.511 --> 00:22:41.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're doing everything possible.

368
00:22:44.590 --> 00:22:46.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll be back as soon as I can.

369
00:22:53.507 --> 00:22:55.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The virus is synthetic, Commander.

370
00:22:55.627 --> 00:22:57.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Its nucleotide sequence is too perfect.

371
00:22:57.906 --> 00:22:59.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's clearly not natural.

372
00:22:59.385 --> 00:23:02.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're saying the Cardassians
genetically engineered this thing?

373
00:23:02.144 --> 00:23:03.504 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, that's what I thought at first,

374
00:23:03.585 --> 00:23:05.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I've studied Cardassian
genetic engineering.

375
00:23:05.703 --> 00:23:08.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They always build distinctive
monoclonial links into their DNA.

376
00:23:08.383 --> 00:23:09.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This virus has none of those features.

377
00:23:10.303 --> 00:23:11.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right, then who made it?

378
00:23:11.542 --> 00:23:12.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, that's what I wanted to find out.

379
00:23:12.861 --> 00:23:15.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So I referenced all known
DNA construction techniques

380
00:23:15.181 --> 00:23:16.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the Federation records

381
00:23:16.660 --> 00:23:18.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and this protein series was the key.

382
00:23:19.139 --> 00:23:20.995 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It indicates--

383
00:23:20.219 --> 00:23:22.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doctor! Who created this virus?

384
00:23:22.298 --> 00:23:23.658 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Bajorans, sir.

385
00:23:24.258 --> 00:23:25.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I believe it must have been
a terrorist plot

386
00:23:25.977 --> 00:23:27.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to sabotage the Cardassians
while they were here.

387
00:23:33.655 --> 00:23:35.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The energy decay of the power core

388
00:23:35.454 --> 00:23:38.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
indicates it dates back
to the building of the station.

389
00:23:38.694 --> 00:23:40.653 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Odo] That's 18 years ago.

390
00:23:40.733 --> 00:23:42.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I suppose the Bajoran underground

391
00:23:42.413 --> 00:23:44.932 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
could have smuggled it aboard
during construction...

392
00:23:45.127 --> 00:23:47.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before I took over as Head of Security.

393
00:23:48.131 --> 00:23:50.211 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But why would the underground
go to all the trouble

394
00:23:50.290 --> 00:23:51.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of planting a booby trap
and not set it off?

395
00:23:52.370 --> 00:23:53.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe they forgot.

396
00:23:53.770 --> 00:23:57.848 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No. More likely, they were captured
or killed before they could release it.

397
00:23:57.928 --> 00:24:00.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We need to find out
who created this virus.

398
00:24:00.967 --> 00:24:02.527 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're our best hope.

399
00:24:03.665 --> 00:24:06.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighing] 18 years is a long time.

400
00:24:06.765 --> 00:24:10.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Besides, even if she finds who did this,
that's no guarantee they can help us.

401
00:24:10.964 --> 00:24:13.438 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We just have to hope
they remember the antidote.

402
00:24:13.203 --> 00:24:15.803 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's assuming they ever
bothered to create one.

403
00:24:23.840 --> 00:24:25.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It had to be someone
in the underground

404
00:24:25.560 --> 00:24:27.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
familiar with genetic engineering.

405
00:24:27.159 --> 00:24:28.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Galis]<i> Eighteen years ago?</i>

406
00:24:28.719 --> 00:24:31.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Sounds like something Dekon Elig</i>
<i>might have thought up.</i>

407
00:24:31.278 --> 00:24:32.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How can I find him?

408
00:24:32.678 --> 00:24:34.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The last I heard</i>
<i>he was in a Cardassian prison.</i>

409
00:24:35.769 --> 00:24:36.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where was he being held?

410
00:24:36.677 --> 00:24:38.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The Velos VII Internment Camp,</i>

411
00:24:38.676 --> 00:24:41.355 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>but that was nine years ago.</i>

412
00:24:43.754 --> 00:24:45.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you have no idea where he is now?

413
00:24:46.738 --> 00:24:47.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Think, Galis! This is important.

414
00:24:48.393 --> 00:24:52.472 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I'm sorry, Kira,</i>
<i>but it was all so long ago.</i>

415
00:24:57.950 --> 00:24:59.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is it, Jake?

416
00:24:59.310 --> 00:25:01.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Roll linger when life.

417
00:25:01.229 --> 00:25:02.589 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Roll linger when...

418
00:25:02.668 --> 00:25:03.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

419
00:25:10.466 --> 00:25:13.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Other support, strong courage...

420
00:25:15.105 --> 00:25:16.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

421
00:25:18.823 --> 00:25:20.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's running a high fever.

422
00:25:20.903 --> 00:25:22.223 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Open way long.

423
00:25:22.303 --> 00:25:23.303 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Open way.

424
00:25:26.422 --> 00:25:28.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Doctor, we have an emergency
in crew quarters.

425
00:25:43.171 --> 00:25:44.256 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How is he, Doctor?

426
00:25:44.336 --> 00:25:45.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not good, I'm afraid.

427
00:25:45.975 --> 00:25:48.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The virus has attacked
his autonomic nervous system.

428
00:25:48.455 --> 00:25:49.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can he be stabilized?

429
00:25:49.895 --> 00:25:51.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He hasn't responded to neural stimulation.

430
00:25:52.254 --> 00:25:55.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've given him 30cc's of corophizine
to avoid secondary infection,

431
00:25:55.533 --> 00:25:57.733 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but so far, I've been unable
to lower his fever.

432
00:25:57.812 --> 00:25:59.531 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are his chances?

433
00:26:01.915 --> 00:26:04.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unless I find some way
to counteract the virus,

434
00:26:05.905 --> 00:26:06.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he'll be dead in 12 hours.

435
00:26:07.689 --> 00:26:09.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have you made any progress?

436
00:26:09.568 --> 00:26:10.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

437
00:26:11.368 --> 00:26:13.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've tried base pair destabilizers,

438
00:26:13.447 --> 00:26:16.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
sequential disruption--
nothing seems to affect it.

439
00:26:17.487 --> 00:26:20.805 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sir, I've got seven other aphasic patients

440
00:26:20.885 --> 00:26:23.404 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
displaying the same symptoms
as O'Brien here,

441
00:26:23.684 --> 00:26:25.804 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and I'm afraid this is only the beginning.

442
00:26:26.484 --> 00:26:28.283 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Keep searching, Doctor.

443
00:26:28.363 --> 00:26:32.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope Major Kira finds whoever's
responsible for creating this virus.

444
00:26:33.822 --> 00:26:35.521 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd like to meet that person myself.

445
00:26:35.600 --> 00:26:37.960 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This virus is a work of genius.

446
00:26:38.409 --> 00:26:39.999 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll try to arrange it for you.

447
00:26:50.396 --> 00:26:52.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[womanr]<i> Link established with</i>
<i>the Bajoran Archival Records.</i>

448
00:26:53.761 --> 00:26:55.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Locate files on Velos VII Internment Camp.

449
00:26:55.635 --> 00:26:56.515 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Ready.</i>

450
00:26:56.594 --> 00:26:59.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you show a record
of an inmate named Dekon Elig?

451
00:26:59.154 --> 00:27:00.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Affirmative.</i>

452
00:27:01.113 --> 00:27:02.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Biographical data.

453
00:27:02.752 --> 00:27:04.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Dekon Elig, geneticist.</i>

454
00:27:04.752 --> 00:27:08.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Former member of the Higa Metar sect</i>
<i>of the Bajoran underground.</i>

455
00:27:08.591 --> 00:27:12.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Killed while attempting escape,</i>
<i>Stardate 39355.</i>

456
00:27:12.790 --> 00:27:14.629 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Certificate of Death on file.</i>

457
00:27:15.669 --> 00:27:17.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No need to ask how you're doing.

458
00:27:17.508 --> 00:27:19.679 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chasing after ghosts.

459
00:27:19.148 --> 00:27:20.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have 12 hours to catch one.

460
00:27:21.747 --> 00:27:22.747 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And then?

461
00:27:22.827 --> 00:27:24.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
People start dying.

462
00:27:30.105 --> 00:27:31.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer...

463
00:27:33.943 --> 00:27:36.143 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
display Dekon Elig's Certificate of Death.

464
00:27:37.862 --> 00:27:40.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Identify signature of witness.

465
00:27:40.262 --> 00:27:43.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[woman]<i> Certificate of Death</i>
<i>was witnessed by Surmak Ren,</i>

466
00:27:43.220 --> 00:27:45.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Bajoran medical assistant.</i>

467
00:27:46.339 --> 00:27:49.579 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Show me biographical data on Surmak Ren.

468
00:27:49.658 --> 00:27:51.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Dr. Surmak Ren.</i>

469
00:27:51.259 --> 00:27:55.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Former member of the Higa Metar sect</i>
<i>of the Bajoran underground.</i>

470
00:27:55.377 --> 00:27:57.456 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Repatriated to Bajor upon closing</i>

471
00:27:57.536 --> 00:28:01.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>of the Velos VII Internment Camp,</i>
<i>Stardate 46302.</i>

472
00:28:02.153 --> 00:28:03.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Current status unknown.</i>

473
00:28:05.574 --> 00:28:08.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[clicking whir]

474
00:28:08.493 --> 00:28:10.652 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[clicking slows]

475
00:28:14.731 --> 00:28:15.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[clicking stops]

476
00:28:16.111 --> 00:28:17.291 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dabo.

477
00:28:23.528 --> 00:28:24.808 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Any luck?

478
00:28:25.886 --> 00:28:27.767 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't won a spin in hours.

479
00:28:29.126 --> 00:28:30.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, care to place a friendly wager?

480
00:28:32.126 --> 00:28:34.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If it's your reputation
you're thinking about,

481
00:28:34.565 --> 00:28:36.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no one need ever know.

482
00:28:36.855 --> 00:28:38.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It has nothing to do with my reputation.

483
00:28:39.683 --> 00:28:41.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

484
00:28:41.283 --> 00:28:43.323 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The truth is, I never...

485
00:28:44.922 --> 00:28:46.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
learned the game.

486
00:28:46.522 --> 00:28:48.241 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You mean, you've sat here
for all these years

487
00:28:48.321 --> 00:28:50.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and you don't even know how to gamble?

488
00:28:50.400 --> 00:28:51.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's correct.

489
00:28:52.240 --> 00:28:54.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No wonder you always look so bored.

490
00:28:55.759 --> 00:28:57.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The rules are quite simple, actually.

491
00:28:57.759 --> 00:28:59.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd be happy to show them to you.

492
00:29:00.598 --> 00:29:02.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Some other time, perhaps.

493
00:29:02.597 --> 00:29:04.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sisko needs me in Ops.

494
00:29:04.477 --> 00:29:08.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And, since the entire security force
has been stricken with aphasia

495
00:29:08.315 --> 00:29:10.874 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the Promenade is in
a very vulnerable position.

496
00:29:11.554 --> 00:29:13.340 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How unfortunate.

497
00:29:14.474 --> 00:29:17.193 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Consider it a warning, Quark.

498
00:29:18.312 --> 00:29:21.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because I'm holding you
personally responsible

499
00:29:21.351 --> 00:29:23.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
if anything turns up missing.

500
00:29:24.790 --> 00:29:26.149 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is that understood?

501
00:29:26.950 --> 00:29:28.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perfectly.

502
00:29:28.549 --> 00:29:29.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm.

503
00:29:38.670 --> 00:29:39.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dabo.

504
00:29:40.465 --> 00:29:43.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, analyze test sample 37 delta.

505
00:29:44.105 --> 00:29:46.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Detail effects on viral containment.

506
00:29:46.504 --> 00:29:48.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]<i> Working.</i>
<i>Analysis complete.</i>

507
00:29:48.983 --> 00:29:51.742 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Sample 37 delta ineffective.</i>

508
00:29:51.822 --> 00:29:54.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Viral protein sheath is unaffected.</i>

509
00:29:54.261 --> 00:29:56.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Nucleotide sequence remains intact.</i>

510
00:29:59.100 --> 00:30:02.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, replay morning.

511
00:30:02.219 --> 00:30:04.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Command unclear. Please repeat.</i>

512
00:30:08.497 --> 00:30:12.136 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Glass lunch judge a bin to let it.

513
00:30:12.215 --> 00:30:14.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Command unclear. Please repeat.</i>

514
00:30:27.171 --> 00:30:31.909 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Computer, establish a link
with the Bajoran Medical Index

515
00:30:31.170 --> 00:30:34.529 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for the, uh, Northwestern District.

516
00:30:34.609 --> 00:30:36.496 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Link established.</i>

517
00:30:36.129 --> 00:30:38.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Access all information on Dr. Surmak Ren.

518
00:30:39.408 --> 00:30:42.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>There are no records matching that name.</i>

519
00:30:42.447 --> 00:30:44.606 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Try the Northeastern District--
same search.

520
00:30:45.206 --> 00:30:47.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Dr. Surmak Ren, currently serving</i>

521
00:30:47.325 --> 00:30:50.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>as Chief Administrator</i>
<i>of the Ilvian Medical Complex.</i>

522
00:30:50.845 --> 00:30:53.884 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Computer, open a channel
to the Ilvian Medical Complex

523
00:30:53.963 --> 00:30:55.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Administrator's office.

524
00:30:57.642 --> 00:31:00.215 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>This is Dr. Surmak. And you are?</i>

525
00:31:00.817 --> 00:31:03.520 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major Kira Nerys,
Bajoran liaison to Deep Space 9.

526
00:31:03.601 --> 00:31:06.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Ah, yes, the old Cardassian</i>
<i>mining station.</i>

527
00:31:06.480 --> 00:31:07.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>How can I help you?</i>

528
00:31:07.799 --> 00:31:09.796 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It depends.

529
00:31:09.159 --> 00:31:10.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>On what?</i>

530
00:31:10.879 --> 00:31:12.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On whether or not you helped Dekon Elig

531
00:31:12.957 --> 00:31:15.277 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
plant an aphasia virus here 18 years ago.

532
00:31:15.877 --> 00:31:18.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I have no idea what you're talking about.</i>

533
00:31:21.835 --> 00:31:24.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look, Sisko, I'm a security officer--
a good one--

534
00:31:24.394 --> 00:31:26.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but that doesn't make me qualified
to help you run station operations.

535
00:31:27.342 --> 00:31:28.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're probably right, Constable.

536
00:31:28.513 --> 00:31:31.352 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But, as you can see,
you're all I've got.

537
00:31:31.432 --> 00:31:33.192 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Kira] Commander...

538
00:31:34.192 --> 00:31:37.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander, I think I found our scientist.

539
00:31:37.471 --> 00:31:38.950 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Does he have an antidote?
-I don't know.

540
00:31:39.301 --> 00:31:40.910 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He broke the connection
the minute I mentioned the virus.

541
00:31:40.989 --> 00:31:42.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major, you mind telling me
where you're going?

542
00:31:43.693 --> 00:31:46.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
To continue my conversation
with Dr. Surmak, in person.

543
00:31:46.508 --> 00:31:48.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major, I can't allow you
to break quarantine.

544
00:31:48.907 --> 00:31:50.307 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We can't risk
spreading the virus to Bajor.

545
00:31:50.386 --> 00:31:51.826 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am well aware of that, Commander.

546
00:31:51.906 --> 00:31:55.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As a matter of fact,
I don't intend to step foot on the planet.

547
00:31:55.745 --> 00:31:57.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Better let her go, Sisko.

548
00:31:58.944 --> 00:32:00.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's all we've got.

549
00:32:11.740 --> 00:32:14.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let's just hope there's someone left
to greet her when she returns.

550
00:32:29.157 --> 00:32:30.255 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jake.

551
00:32:32.147 --> 00:32:33.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How's it going?

552
00:32:46.290 --> 00:32:48.958 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've missed you.

553
00:32:48.809 --> 00:32:51.249 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know things don't look
too good right now,

554
00:32:51.688 --> 00:32:53.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but they'll get better.

555
00:32:54.167 --> 00:32:56.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have to believe that...

556
00:32:57.367 --> 00:32:59.886 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because I'm not going
to lose you, Jake.

557
00:33:00.846 --> 00:33:02.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You hear me?

558
00:33:02.924 --> 00:33:04.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not going to lose you.

559
00:33:20.405 --> 00:33:21.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You better take a look at this.

560
00:33:21.359 --> 00:33:23.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We have activity on Docking Port 5.

561
00:33:23.198 --> 00:33:24.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think a ship is about to depart.

562
00:33:24.718 --> 00:33:26.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Docking Port 5? That's Jaheel's ship.

563
00:33:26.637 --> 00:33:28.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Put him on screen.

564
00:33:32.955 --> 00:33:36.234 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, your ship has
not been cleared for departure.

565
00:33:36.355 --> 00:33:37.634 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The mooring clamps are locked,

566
00:33:37.715 --> 00:33:39.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and I don't intend to release them.

567
00:33:39.834 --> 00:33:41.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I suggest you change your mind.</i>

568
00:33:42.113 --> 00:33:44.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I'm taking aft thrusters to one half.</i>

569
00:33:47.712 --> 00:33:50.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, cut your engines
before you rip your ship apart.

570
00:33:52.303 --> 00:33:53.509 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's not reducing power.

571
00:33:54.303 --> 00:33:57.293 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jaheel, I'm ordering you to stand down.

572
00:33:57.108 --> 00:33:59.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Your orders are no concern of mine.</i>

573
00:33:59.267 --> 00:34:02.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>My entire crew has been</i>
<i>confined to your hospital.</i>

574
00:34:02.147 --> 00:34:04.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I must leave now</i>
<i>while I can still function.</i>

575
00:34:05.262 --> 00:34:08.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look, I understand that you're frightened
but believe me, you're better off here.

576
00:34:09.654 --> 00:34:11.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don't want to be out there alone
and get hit by the virus.

577
00:34:11.824 --> 00:34:14.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Don't worry about me, I'm fine.</i>

578
00:34:15.423 --> 00:34:17.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And I plan to stay that way.</i>

579
00:34:18.231 --> 00:34:19.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-And if you think you're go--
-[cuts transmission]

580
00:34:22.221 --> 00:34:23.540 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We'll have to retract the clamps.

581
00:34:23.621 --> 00:34:27.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Once he's clear of the station
we can grab him with a tractor beam.

582
00:34:33.817 --> 00:34:35.377 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Damn.
-What's wrong?

583
00:34:35.497 --> 00:34:37.217 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's too much stress
on the mooring clamps.

584
00:34:37.296 --> 00:34:38.616 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're not retracting.

585
00:34:39.176 --> 00:34:41.336 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groaning]

586
00:34:41.495 --> 00:34:43.814 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[console beeping]

587
00:34:44.455 --> 00:34:46.774 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His aft isolation plate buckled.

588
00:34:47.334 --> 00:34:49.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His main power core's been ruptured.

589
00:34:49.653 --> 00:34:52.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If the internal fuel cells collapse,
the whole ship will explode.

590
00:34:52.572 --> 00:34:55.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And take half the docking ring with it.

591
00:35:05.368 --> 00:35:07.480 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, isolate a com line

592
00:35:07.127 --> 00:35:10.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to the Ilvian Medical Complex
Administrator's office.

593
00:35:10.367 --> 00:35:12.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[female voice on computer]<i> Line isolated.</i>

594
00:35:12.206 --> 00:35:14.459 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Scan office for life-forms.

595
00:35:14.125 --> 00:35:16.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>One life-form present.</i>

596
00:35:16.685 --> 00:35:19.842 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lock on and stand by to transport.

597
00:35:21.523 --> 00:35:24.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>-This is Dr. Surmak.</i>
-Hello again, Doctor.

598
00:35:24.203 --> 00:35:26.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just checking to see
you're in your office.

599
00:35:26.522 --> 00:35:27.922 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I have nothing to say to you--</i>

600
00:35:35.439 --> 00:35:37.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello again, Doctor.

601
00:35:37.478 --> 00:35:39.238 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is outrageous.

602
00:35:39.318 --> 00:35:41.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I demand you return me
to my office immediately.

603
00:35:41.957 --> 00:35:44.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Relax, Doctor. You won't be gone long.

604
00:35:49.875 --> 00:35:52.514 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Try to reestablish visual contact
with Jaheel's ship.

605
00:35:55.739 --> 00:35:57.113 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Odo] No response. His com lines are down.

606
00:35:57.312 --> 00:35:59.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bypass communications
through a secondary grid.

607
00:36:00.719 --> 00:36:02.510 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
See if you can switch
to external pickups.

608
00:36:02.871 --> 00:36:03.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Got it.

609
00:36:06.509 --> 00:36:09.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
His fire control systems
don't appear to be working.

610
00:36:10.149 --> 00:36:13.548 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have about 15 minutes
before the fuel cells collapse.

611
00:36:14.987 --> 00:36:17.186 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope you feel better than you look.

612
00:36:17.786 --> 00:36:20.657 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Must be that damn virus.

613
00:36:20.345 --> 00:36:21.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is Sisko.

614
00:36:22.425 --> 00:36:25.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Any station personnel who can understand
what I'm saying, come to Ops immediately.

615
00:36:25.824 --> 00:36:27.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We need help up here.

616
00:36:27.383 --> 00:36:29.503 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have to get that ship
away from the station.

617
00:36:29.783 --> 00:36:31.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why don't we explode
the mooring clamps?

618
00:36:31.782 --> 00:36:34.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The blast should push the ship
away from the docking ring.

619
00:36:34.381 --> 00:36:36.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll have to get down there
and blow it manually.

620
00:36:36.820 --> 00:36:38.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

621
00:36:38.260 --> 00:36:39.539 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll do it.

622
00:36:40.620 --> 00:36:41.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

623
00:36:42.419 --> 00:36:43.699 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can cross barrels.

624
00:36:44.859 --> 00:36:46.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All job appalled.

625
00:36:47.217 --> 00:36:48.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What was that?

626
00:36:49.976 --> 00:36:51.565 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bread...

627
00:36:51.177 --> 00:36:52.576 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the arrive...

628
00:36:52.656 --> 00:36:54.535 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
seen earlier.

629
00:36:56.295 --> 00:36:58.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I see.

630
00:37:07.251 --> 00:37:09.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Major, this is kidnapping.

631
00:37:09.916 --> 00:37:11.210 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Turn this ship around
or I swear you will spend

632
00:37:11.331 --> 00:37:13.730 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the rest of your life
in Kran-Tobol Prison.

633
00:37:13.809 --> 00:37:16.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fine. But first, we need your help.

634
00:37:17.895 --> 00:37:19.648 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The aphasia virus is spreading
through the station.

635
00:37:19.728 --> 00:37:21.127 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why come to me?

636
00:37:21.448 --> 00:37:23.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You helped create the virus, didn't you?

637
00:37:23.327 --> 00:37:25.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, I had practically
nothing to do with it.

638
00:37:25.366 --> 00:37:27.206 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dekon Elig created the virus.

639
00:37:27.285 --> 00:37:29.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was merely his medical assistant.

640
00:37:29.445 --> 00:37:31.364 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That seems like a lifetime ago now.

641
00:37:31.684 --> 00:37:33.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was only in the underground
for six months

642
00:37:33.804 --> 00:37:35.203 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before we were captured.

643
00:37:35.324 --> 00:37:37.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am not responsible for this.

644
00:37:37.243 --> 00:37:38.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am not looking to place blame!

645
00:37:38.882 --> 00:37:40.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All I want is the antidote.

646
00:37:41.601 --> 00:37:43.560 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't know of any antidote.

647
00:37:43.641 --> 00:37:45.920 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If Dekon created one, he never told me.

648
00:37:46.759 --> 00:37:47.240 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Listen, Surmak.

649
00:37:47.559 --> 00:37:49.479 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have a station full of dying people

650
00:37:49.559 --> 00:37:53.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and you are the closest thing there is
to an expert on this virus.

651
00:37:53.358 --> 00:37:54.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I sympathize, Major,

652
00:37:54.997 --> 00:37:56.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but I don't think I can help you.

653
00:37:57.876 --> 00:37:59.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

654
00:38:00.595 --> 00:38:02.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then how about helping yourself?

655
00:38:03.115 --> 00:38:04.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Meaning what?

656
00:38:04.754 --> 00:38:05.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Meaning...

657
00:38:07.153 --> 00:38:10.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been infected
with your virus, Doctor...

658
00:38:11.793 --> 00:38:13.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so now you're infected, too.

659
00:38:19.150 --> 00:38:21.909 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
To anyone who can hear me, this is Odo.

660
00:38:21.989 --> 00:38:22.989 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sisko's infected.

661
00:38:23.690 --> 00:38:25.108 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I could really use some help here in Ops.

662
00:38:25.229 --> 00:38:28.707 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do I detect a note of panic in your voice?

663
00:38:28.788 --> 00:38:29.906 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quark.

664
00:38:30.387 --> 00:38:33.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Am I to believe that you're
volunteering to help?

665
00:38:33.706 --> 00:38:35.985 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who said anything about volunteering?

666
00:38:36.649 --> 00:38:38.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We can haggle over price later.

667
00:38:38.544 --> 00:38:39.744 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now, um...

668
00:38:40.343 --> 00:38:42.663 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
how may I be of use?

669
00:38:43.103 --> 00:38:45.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I need to get to Docking Port 5 now.

670
00:38:45.342 --> 00:38:47.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That ship's going to explode
in five minutes.

671
00:38:48.618 --> 00:38:49.261 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll beam you over.

672
00:38:49.500 --> 00:38:51.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You?
-Relax.

673
00:38:51.700 --> 00:38:55.299 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I served on a Ferengi freighter
for eight years.

674
00:38:56.459 --> 00:38:57.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

675
00:38:58.259 --> 00:39:01.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I must have witnessed the procedure
hundreds of times.

676
00:39:01.777 --> 00:39:05.416 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Witnessed? You mean to say you never
handled the controls yourself?

677
00:39:05.537 --> 00:39:06.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Energizing!

678
00:39:14.143 --> 00:39:15.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighing]

679
00:39:24.851 --> 00:39:27.410 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Kira to Ops. Approaching Landing Pad 7.

680
00:39:27.489 --> 00:39:29.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Request clearance
to initiate docking procedure.

681
00:39:29.808 --> 00:39:32.488 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Quark]<i> Welcome back.</i>
<i>I could use some help up here.</i>

682
00:39:32.568 --> 00:39:35.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quark, what are you doing in Ops?

683
00:39:35.567 --> 00:39:37.474 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing]

684
00:39:41.205 --> 00:39:42.365 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
First thing I need to see

685
00:39:42.445 --> 00:39:44.964 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is your doctor's viral
characterization research.

686
00:39:48.724 --> 00:39:50.443 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He was beginning to develop
an antidote series.

687
00:39:50.522 --> 00:39:51.922 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's take a look at that.

688
00:39:52.303 --> 00:39:53.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Kira] Listen, Doctor, um...

689
00:39:53.801 --> 00:39:54.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll be in Ops.

690
00:39:54.921 --> 00:39:57.201 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you need me, use this string impact.

691
00:39:58.120 --> 00:39:59.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lot show red intense.

692
00:40:01.200 --> 00:40:03.639 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think you'd better sit down, Major.

693
00:40:07.557 --> 00:40:09.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[alarm wailing]

694
00:40:22.193 --> 00:40:24.913 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Jaheel] Dog fellow distance.

695
00:40:24.992 --> 00:40:26.512 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Odo] Yeah, tell me about it.

696
00:40:26.591 --> 00:40:28.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark]<i> Odo, you'd better hurry up.</i>

697
00:40:28.671 --> 00:40:30.830 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That ship's going to explode
in one minute.

698
00:40:34.149 --> 00:40:35.750 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Virum protein sheath.

699
00:40:36.749 --> 00:40:38.469 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nucleotide sequence.

700
00:40:39.308 --> 00:40:40.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

701
00:40:40.348 --> 00:40:41.387 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's right.

702
00:40:41.468 --> 00:40:43.627 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's an adaptive, synaptic inhibitor.

703
00:40:44.187 --> 00:40:45.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dekon was brilliant.

704
00:40:45.626 --> 00:40:47.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No doubt of that.

705
00:40:47.266 --> 00:40:50.584 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think we've found your antidote, Major.

706
00:40:53.144 --> 00:40:54.784 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark]<i> 40 seconds.</i>

707
00:41:07.579 --> 00:41:08.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
30 seconds. Hurry!

708
00:41:09.219 --> 00:41:10.858 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I know, I know.

709
00:41:15.337 --> 00:41:17.137 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
20 seconds!

710
00:41:22.615 --> 00:41:24.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ten seconds!

711
00:41:24.535 --> 00:41:26.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[alarm blares]

712
00:41:26.374 --> 00:41:27.254 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

713
00:41:48.447 --> 00:41:50.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark]<i> Odo? Quark to Odo.</i>

714
00:41:50.366 --> 00:41:51.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You still with us?

715
00:41:52.166 --> 00:41:54.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Try not to sound too disappointed.

716
00:41:54.605 --> 00:41:57.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, about that little matter
of my hazard pay...

717
00:41:58.524 --> 00:42:00.204 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why, you...

718
00:42:04.242 --> 00:42:06.241 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on. Come on.

719
00:42:10.415 --> 00:42:13.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sisko]<i> Station Log, Stardate 46425.8.</i>

720
00:42:13.919 --> 00:42:15.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>With the help of Dr. Bashir's notes,</i>

721
00:42:15.599 --> 00:42:18.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Dr. Surmak was able to find</i>
<i>an antidote for the aphasia virus.</i>

722
00:42:18.998 --> 00:42:21.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We are continuing to administer</i>
<i>it throughout the station</i>

723
00:42:21.998 --> 00:42:24.597 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and things are slowly</i>
<i>returning to normal.</i>

724
00:42:24.676 --> 00:42:26.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good to have you back, Chief.

725
00:42:26.276 --> 00:42:27.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you, sir.

726
00:42:27.756 --> 00:42:28.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Coffee, black.

727
00:42:35.833 --> 00:42:36.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
O'Brien!

